ABUJA – Ahead of Osun state governorship election, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) on Wednesday screened Senator Ademola Adeleke, Akin Ogunbiyi, Dele Adeleke, Emmanuel Oluseye, Dotun Babayemi and Fatai Akinbade for the party primary scheduled for March 9, 2022. Speaking with journalists shortly after the screening, former Minister of Justice and Attorney General of Federation (AGF), Mohammed Adoke, who chaired the screening, disclosed that the report of the screening will be submitted to party leadership within forty-eight hours. Noting that there were few petitions against Dele Adeleke, Adoke, who didn’t give details of the petitions, added that the panel ensured that the process was transparent. 2023: Orji Uzor Kalu Wants Presidency Zoned To South-East NAF Special Forces Rescue Kidnap Victims He said: “I can assure you that we shall turn in our report by the next 48hours. Six of them turned in for the screening and we screened all of them and we are satisfied with the answers they gave us. “We ensured that the process was transparent. We ensured that they were given fair hearing and we ensured that we executed the mandate given to us by the party. We ensured that we worked with the dictates of our conscience and dictates of fairness. “As a party in opposition preparing to win the next election, we ensured we built the necessary trust within the party members so that we can work in tandem with our objective which is to win the Osun State election.” Ogunbiyi, who also spoke with journalists said, “I’m very optimistic. The panel is made up of people of integrity. They have done this in the past. I’m very confident that justice will be done.